item.name: Transport for London Unified API Client
Transport for London Unified API Client

task.summary: Added filter fnctioning for relationship querying on the beginning and ending nodes. Main Tube1 program now minimizes segment creation by reusing whereever possible. Added javadocs that were missing.
reduce number of duplicate relationships by only mapping inbound and not outbound, since in the majority (all?) cases there is always an inbound/outbound match
Functionality added to allow running demo without network connection
Best practice is for upper-case relationship labels
Changed so relationship to client - FILED -> filings, which makes more sense from a left-to-right perspective, added some more queries
Changed to load all filings contained within zip file
Documented query files a little better after confirming all queries worked as designed.
updated json files for routes, do not do overall route relationships but only line-detail with segments
segment-based TFL tube graph instead of putting labels on the stops
new module for segment-based TFL underground instead of stop-based with labels
